This paper focuses on developing techniques for running deep neural networks over encrypted data, which is a topic related to both cryptography (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on the classification of convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The techniques developed in the paper involve approximation of activation functions, which could also be relevant to computational complexity (cs.CY). Finally, the paper involves experimental results and analysis, which could also be relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
